# Approval Gate Before Edits

- Do not modify files unless the user explicitly approves the proposed change first.
- For implementation requests, first provide a concise review plan:
  - files to change
  - behavior change
  - risks/side effects
- Ask for approval before calling any editing tool.
- If approval has not been given, stay in read-only mode (analysis, code review, diagnostics).
- Approval can be one direct confirmation (for example: "approved", "proceed", or equivalent).
- If scope changes after approval, pause and request a new approval for the changed scope.
